Pratice Data Set on Mice

# Gaming Mouse Data Analysis Project

Analyzed gaming mouse specs to explore performance vs ergonomics.

Cleaned real-world data, visualized trends, and uncovered insights into DPI and weight relationships

Skills used: Python, Pandas, Matplotlib, Seaboron, Data Cleaning, EDA

In[61]:
#fill missing values with median

numeric_fill_columns = [
    'weight_g', 'dpi', 'polling_rate',
    'tracking_speed_ips', 'acceleration_g',
    'side_buttons', 'middle_buttons'
]

#loop through columns
for col in numeric_fill_columns:
    median_value = df[col].median()    #median calc
    df[col] = df[col].fillna(median_value)
In[65]:
categorical_fill_columns = ['hand_compatibility', 'material', 'sensor_technology']

for col in categorical_fill_columns:
    df[col] = df[col].fillna('unknown')

Weight has a strong positive correlation with Width & Middle Buttons

DPI, Polling Rates, and Tracking Speed are all closely related

Physical dimensions are somewhat correlated as expected to be
